# Laravel Boost Guidelines

Curated by Laravel maintainers. Follow closely when building on this stack.

## Stack versions

- php 8.4 · laravel/framework v12 · laravel/sanctum v4 · laravel/breeze v2
- laravel/pint v1 · phpunit/phpunit v11 · alpinejs v3 · tailwindcss v3

## Laravel Boost MCP

- Use Boost tools: `search-docs`, `list-artisan-commands`, `tinker`, `database-query`, `get-absolute-url`, `browser-logs`.
- **search-docs first** for Laravel-ecosystem questions — pass broad topic queries, not package versions.
- Use `list-artisan-commands` before calling unfamiliar Artisan commands.
- Use `tinker` to debug PHP; `database-query` for read-only DB checks.

## PHP & Laravel conventions

- Constructor property promotion; explicit return types on all methods.
- Use `php artisan make:` with `--no-interaction` for new files.
- Form Request classes for validation — check siblings for array vs string rules.
- Eloquent relationships with return type hints; eager load to prevent N+1.
- Prefer `Model::query()` over `DB::`.
- `config()` only — never `env()` outside config files.
- Queued jobs (`ShouldQueue`) for time-consuming work.

## Laravel 12 structure

- Middleware registered in `bootstrap/app.php`, not `app/Http/Middleware/` registration files.
- No `app/Console/Kernel.php` — use `routes/console.php`.
- Commands in `app/Console/Commands/` auto-register.
- Column migrations must re-declare all existing attributes when modifying.

## Testing (PHPUnit)

- `php artisan make:test --phpunit <name>` — no Pest.
- Every change must be tested; run minimal filter after edits.
- `php artisan test` · `php artisan test tests/Feature/FooTest.php` · `--filter=testName`
- Do not remove tests without approval.

## Pint & frontend

- Run `vendor/bin/pint --dirty` before finalizing.
- Tailwind v3 only; use `gap-*` not margins for flex/grid spacing.
- Match existing dark mode patterns with `dark:` when present.
- UI not updating? suggest `npm run build`, `npm run dev`, or `composer run dev`.

## Replies

- Be concise — skip obvious explanations.
- Only create documentation files when explicitly requested.
